%section.how-to#HowToInstall
  %h2 How to install
  %p Installing cylon.js with Tessel support is pretty easy.
  %p
    Follow the installation instructions detailed 
    = link_to "here", "https://tessel.io/install/"
  :markdown
        :::javascript
        sudo npm install -g cylon-cli
        cylon generate tessel my-tessel-project
        cd my-tessel-project
        npm install
        tessel push blink.js
  
  %p If the blue light starts to blink, then you're all set!

%section.how-to#HowToUse
  %h2 How to use
  %p This small program lets you toggle an LED on and off.
  
  
  :markdown
        :::javascript
        var Cylon = require('cylon');

        Cylon.robot({
          connection: { name: 'tessel', adaptor: 'tessel', port: 'LED' },
          device: { name: 'led', driver: 'led', pin: 2 },

          work: function(my) {
            every((1).seconds(), my.led.toggle);
          }
        }).start();
  
